    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >😘Face To Face is a satisfying action puzzle game that combines the Physics of Suika Game with a SUPER COOL Set Matching mechanic.😅 </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >🟦<strong>How to Play🟪</strong> </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >1. Tap Shapes to give them a face.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >2. When faces touch, They kiss and disappear!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >3. Faces can kiss through other objects, as long as each shape has one thing in common with the one before.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >(this would be a valid example -&gt; 😘🟡🟢🟩🟨😅)</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >4. Create longer chains for more points.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >🟦<strong>About the developer🟪</strong>  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Samuel Leigh is a game developer, writer and adjunct professor based in New York. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >His work spans from Interactive fiction, to puzzle and action games. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >His other games, Conversation with a Rock, Annoy this Guy, The Way Down, Blow Out and Moving Jigsaw Puzzles can be played on Steam now!</p>",
